The paper deals with image restoration, specifically the removal of Moire patterns from digital images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of multi-scale networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.MM) for processing images at different resolutions. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of dealing with dynamic textures, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The proposed method also involves feature encoding, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
